Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.12,0:00:07.30,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Act 11\NThe Adventure of the Pistol Daimyo\N~Bullet Counting Song~"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.98,0:00:07.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.65,0:00:11.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is going on?!\NWho do these carriages belong to?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.82,0:00:15.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They belong to the powerful \NCount Saint-Germi.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.47,0:00:17.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you not tell from the banner?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.08,0:00:20.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whom do you think you are telling to stop?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.33,0:00:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.33,0:00:24.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.25,0:00:27.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You dare stop lord Saint-Germi's carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.13,0:00:30.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll certainly be sent\Nto the front lines tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.71,0:00:32.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me your name.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.72,0:00:35.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,P-Please continue on.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.68,0:00:40.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Lord Saint-Germi can no longer\Nsit back and watch this war unfold;
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.01,0:00:43.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,therefore, her highness will join the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.14,0:00:46.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Many more carriages will be following us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.31,0:00:48.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She will save Orte.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.94,0:00:50.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah... It's about time...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.23,0:00:53.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Open the gate. Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.53,0:01:03.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Join the war"... Not a \Nsingle thing was false.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.50,0:01:07.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, we won't be on their side.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.50,0:01:12.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, this is the capital of Orte, Verlina.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.38,0:01:16.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have to make this place our capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.76,0:01:24.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's pathetic to see a country like this\Nfall from grace so miserably.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.48,0:01:26.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It should just be burned away quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.31,0:01:34.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true. It would be a pity\Nnot to put an end to its suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.24,0:01:37.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Coup d'etat"?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.99,0:01:40.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is "coup d'etat"?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.11,0:01:42.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it some sort of food \Nfor southern barbarians?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.08,0:01:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a coup.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.66,0:01:46.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reins of power are seized\Nthrough an assault on the state's capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.16,0:01:51.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will guide you the entire way.\NI will sell you the whole country.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.71,0:01:53.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it a great deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.09,0:01:56.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is your leader?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.68,0:02:02.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how it happened,\Nbut it's supposed to be me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.97,0:02:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is your... What are your names?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.48,0:02:10.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you are Drifters, I may be able\Nto recognize your names.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.65,0:02:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Shimazu Toyohisa, undersecretary to\Nthe Imperial Minister of the Center.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.73,0:02:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toyohisa Shimazu... Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.94,0:02:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, the Battle of Sekigahara in 1600.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.12,0:02:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Nasu Suketaka Yoichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.95,0:02:26.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How cute! You are the archer\Nfrom the Genpei War.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.41,0:02:28.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are famous, don't you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.40,0:02:29.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.56,0:02:31.20,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Rumble rumble rumble"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.58,0:02:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oda Nobunaga!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.46,0:02:34.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are super famous!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.29,0:02:37.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. That's the way it should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.01,0:02:38.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is that old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.01,0:02:41.72,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Raspberry Sensor" "Dazed"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.76,0:02:41.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know his name.\NHe's just a raspberry man.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.80,0:02:48.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like you've been sent from a time\Nlong after the periods we lived in, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.14,0:02:53.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to know what happened\Nto the Shimazu clan after Sekigahara?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.77,0:02:56.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind telling you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.03,0:02:58.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to tell me that.\NI know what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.90,0:03:01.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My uncle, Yoshihiro,\Nshould have been able to escape
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.86,0:03:05.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from the enemy while we were\Nfighting to buy time for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.37,0:03:08.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he returned to Satsuma,\NI know what happened after that...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.37,0:03:12.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Shimazu destroyed the Tokugawa clan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.04,0:03:14.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how long it took--\Ntens or hundreds of years--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.00,0:03:18.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but without doubt, the Shimazu\Nsoldiers crashed the Tokugawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.84,0:03:20.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh--?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.13,0:03:22.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with this kid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.13,0:03:26.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could he predict such an outcome\Nin the midst of withdrawal?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.39,0:03:28.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has got some nerve.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.52,0:03:33.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... that's just how he is.\NI apologize for him, Twinkie.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.06,0:03:37.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, how about me?\NMe? How am I remembered?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.02,0:03:39.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no way to describe\Nyour impact succinctly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.65,0:03:43.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You increased in size and flew through\Nthe air shooting mysterious beams...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.53,0:03:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Increased in size...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.08,0:03:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and brought hell to earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.91,0:03:49.12,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"For Love"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.16,0:03:49.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and made green tea with bisected bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.12,0:03:51.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You are more famous for weapon innovation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.31,0:03:52.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What weapons?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.62,0:03:54.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened in the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.46,0:03:58.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you trust that\Nandrogynous person?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.71,0:03:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.64,0:04:02.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you will meet that kind\Nevery now and then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.18,0:04:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They will betray you without any hesitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.31,0:04:09.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are devoid of fidelity\Nand loyalty from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.72,0:04:15.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, their betrayal is motivated\Nby profit and self-interest,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.52,0:04:17.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,not resentment or\Ngenerational sentimentality.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.19,0:04:22.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we can trust them as long\Nas they are betraying someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.88,0:04:27.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a strange story. They are peculiar\Nnot only outside, but also inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.49,0:04:31.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are bizarre. They are weird,\Nbody and soul. They are weirdos.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.75,0:04:33.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are deviants.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.79,0:04:37.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can hear you, Japanese! Hush up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.50,0:04:39.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Count Saint-Germi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.21,0:04:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd like to know why you used \Nyour authority as a powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.91,0:04:44.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,count to call this meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.68,0:04:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you wait till the\Nsituation became so dire?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.81,0:04:52.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to inform you...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.94,0:04:57.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...of the shutting down of Orte.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.86,0:05:07.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We Drifters created this nation\Nwith great diligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.66,0:05:10.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have lent you this country\Nfor a half a century,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.62,0:05:12.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I am sorry. I can do it no longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.04,0:05:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, I've decided \Nto have you return it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.12,0:05:19.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As of today, we are closing\Nthe experimental empire, Orte.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.92,0:05:22.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are closing the store.\NWe are going out of business.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.42,0:05:29.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will turn over a new leaf and work hard\Nwith Toyohisa as our future leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.93,0:05:33.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, thank you for your\Nmany years of patronage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.40,0:05:35.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Farewell.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.77,0:05:39.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What?! What are you saying,\NCount Saint-Germi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.56,0:05:41.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.22,0:05:44.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I explained it to you in the simplest \Npossible terms, did I not?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.36,0:05:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you an imbecile?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.32,0:05:48.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, you do look like one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.49,0:05:53.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guards! Guards! Count Saint-Germi\Nhas lost his mind. Guards!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.87,0:05:56.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how much you yell,\Nthey won't be coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.66,0:06:00.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you stupid?\NIndeed, you do look damn stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.10,0:06:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saint-Germi! This is a coup. A revolt!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.60,0:06:21.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Against whom--Father or the politicians?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.94,0:06:25.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is for my plan? Speak up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.07,0:06:28.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I support Count Saint-Germi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.53,0:06:29.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.78,0:06:31.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am with the count.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.03,0:06:32.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh... What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.83,0:06:33.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.91,0:06:38.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you really think I convened this\Nmeeting without any preparation?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.04,0:06:39.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you that stupid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.79,0:06:44.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you two over there...\NFully raise your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.21,0:06:48.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I agree with the dissolution\Nof the empire's leadership.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.47,0:06:50.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahh, that's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.84,0:06:52.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.01,0:06:52.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.10,0:06:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I am against any plan in which we\Nappoint a Drifter as the head of state.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.52,0:07:02.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All sovereignty in the new country\Nshall be given to the Black King.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.77,0:07:07.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can solely prostrate ourselves,\Nbegging the Black King for his mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.74,0:07:09.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us be his vanguard
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.65,0:07:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and help him in the campaign for the\Neradication of humankind from this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.37,0:07:17.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rasputin! So, you became an End, huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.00,0:07:22.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Count Saint-Germi, we both\Nseem to have had similar ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.87,0:07:25.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You still look ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.95,0:07:30.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are completely wrong if\Nyou think you can get your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.06,0:07:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What... What on earth is going on?!\NThis is not what I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.69,0:07:47.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, these are the faces of the Drifters.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.57,0:07:50.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that you took care\Nof Joan and Gilles de Rais.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.61,0:07:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Rasputin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.78,0:07:59.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Frankly, the Black Lord is too busy\Nto be bothered with you all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.25,0:08:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For you see, he is bringing about\Nthe destruction of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.96,0:08:08.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, I am carrying out\Nhis plan. For instance...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.51,0:08:14.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We let our troops into the capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.39,0:08:22.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, they may be a bit troublesome.\NI sincerely apologize for...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.83,0:08:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now he's done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.00,0:08:53.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, you are the leader of\Nthe Drifters, Shimazu Toyohisa.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.80,0:08:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suddenly drawing a sword,\Nsuddenly launching an assault...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.30,0:09:00.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to be from quite a barbaric place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.35,0:09:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must express my gratitude to you\Nfor taking care of our comrade, Joan...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.15,0:09:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch, this is harsh. I don't know\Nwho he is, but my condolences to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.20,0:09:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know it hurts when things like this happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.04,0:09:25.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At his moment of glory, right as he was\Nabout to gloat like a puppet master,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.29,0:09:29.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he was completely ignored while\Nhis minion was crushed before him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.46,0:09:32.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That kind of thing is utterly humiliating.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.88,0:09:34.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toyo doesn't read the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.22,0:09:37.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that he can't--he just won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.21,0:09:39.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He completely shuts it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.80,0:09:42.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than being in his \Nnature, perhaps this comes
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.80,0:09:45.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from the way he was brought up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.64,0:09:49.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is his strongest weapon\Nas well as his greatest weakness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.81,0:09:52.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he's not careful,\Nhe'll be dead before he knows it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.73,0:09:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toyo, sweetie, wait. Hold it.\NYou will kill him. He'll die.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.16,0:10:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you flinch even a little, you'll lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.25,0:10:08.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Smile. Keep smiling, you fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.96,0:10:11.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Mr. Would-Be Puppet Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.05,0:10:13.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your smile is stiff.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.04,0:10:15.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Allow us to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.22,0:10:17.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.76,0:10:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our intention from the beginning is to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.51,0:10:23.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will kill anyone who stands in our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.28,0:10:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never conquered a territory\Nwithout shedding blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.31,0:10:30.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your true intention was to snatch\Nthis country bloodlessly, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.06,0:10:34.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our being here really puts a\Nsour look on your face, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.48,0:10:38.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even that twinkie count's sour face\Nis more likable than yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.15,0:10:42.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we can address the threat of the Ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.62,0:10:45.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We, the Drifters, have come\Nto save the country again...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.25,0:10:50.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for giving us such a\Nperfectly legitimate reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.71,0:10:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's with the grimace?!\NSmile like you did earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.88,0:10:59.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Smile! Smile like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.56,0:11:08.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are going to settle this in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.06,0:11:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shoot! Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.19,0:11:18.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! That bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.11,0:11:21.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come in, Rasputin. Answer me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.57,0:11:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Verlina has already been\Noccupied by the Drifters!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.91,0:11:27.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We manipulated the aristocrats and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.77,0:11:30.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,had our troops make the \Nlong march on Verlina.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.08,0:11:32.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even for our army,\Nwhich is capable of a massive blitz,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.25,0:11:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Drifters are an unexpected variable!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.25,0:11:40.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never expected them to\Ntake such decisive action.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.72,0:11:44.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are crazy. They are absurd--\Ncompletely out of their minds!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.30,0:11:49.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep calm, Rasputin. This is war.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.98,0:11:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We cannot always foresee the outcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.04,0:11:53.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Things will happen outside your expectation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.57,0:11:55.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is what war is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.15,0:11:59.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave everything to me. I will conquer Orte.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.07,0:12:03.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, we may be already corrupted.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.53,0:12:05.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hijikata.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.91,0:12:08.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rasputin.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.70,0:12:12.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the conquest of Verlina is\Ndetermined to be unattainable,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.50,0:12:15.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then at your discretion, change the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.38,0:12:17.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aim for destruction instead of usurpation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.88,0:12:21.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our objective shall be\Nmaximum destruction and chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.22,0:12:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kill as many as you can.\NBurn as much as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.35,0:12:28.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My intention is to stop the Drifters\Nfrom taking control of the state,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.81,0:12:31.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but if it falls into their hands, cripple it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.52,0:12:33.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.77,0:12:35.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thy will be done...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.35,0:12:37.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black Majesty, you're fearsome.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.11,0:12:41.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bring me a map of Verlina! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.11,0:12:46.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was just my old habit,\Nbut I was a bit too arrogant.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.41,0:12:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I lose, it will be no laughing matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.53,0:12:52.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't seen such a conceited look\Nin the past several centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.58,0:12:55.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two hundred Elves and two hundred Dwarves.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.21,0:12:57.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't say anything at this point since\NI don't know the size of the enemy forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.92,0:13:01.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was the most I could sneak in,\Nhiding in the carriages.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.26,0:13:06.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The troops I have waiting outside\Nthe capital should be heading this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.89,0:13:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They should be arriving any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.60,0:13:11.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are an elite unit,\Nconsisting of 500 soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.43,0:13:14.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn twinkie! In situations like this,\Nyou should send more troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.85,0:13:17.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It should've been enough force\Nif it were just a normal coup!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.65,0:13:18.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You hear me?! I said "normal"!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.98,0:13:21.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, that is the \Nentire army in my domain!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.15,0:13:33.62,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Grind grind"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.40,0:13:25.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! Y-You call that an \Narmy?! With only 500?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.24,0:13:28.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you a powerful lord of Orte?\NHow do you explain that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.78,0:13:31.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I selected only the best,\Nthat was all I could find.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.54,0:13:33.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My troops are so much tougher than others!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.79,0:13:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Count Saint-Germi,\Nyour army has just arrived outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.29,0:13:37.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.29,0:13:38.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.58,0:13:39.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.76,0:13:45.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your troops certainly look tough, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.63,0:13:50.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...something is odd. Why \Nare they all topless?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.26,0:13:54.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I happened to notice that already.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.85,0:13:56.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, damn twinkie!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.35,0:13:58.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope they are not what I think \Nthey are... but what are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.65,0:14:02.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That's right! They are\Nthe Sacred Band of Thebes!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.15,0:14:05.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-So what?! It is not your concern\Nhow I assemble my forces!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.69,0:14:07.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have anything to say about that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.66,0:14:09.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, this is the reason he \Nhas so few troops relative
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.57,0:14:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to the size of his territory, huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.57,0:14:13.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure enough, he picked carefully!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.15,0:14:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise, this result \Nwould have been impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.45,0:14:17.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, where is the restroom?\NI am going to throw up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.50,0:14:20.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[in Latin] The Sacred Band of Thebes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.71,0:14:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do... Do you know about that,\Nold man? Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.13,0:14:27.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[in Latin] Echelon Formation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.13,0:14:30.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two-bit thief! Two-bit thief of Gorgidas!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.13,0:21:54.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.64,0:14:33.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the heck is this old \Nfool?! Is he senile?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.56,0:14:35.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No clue! I don't know anything \Nabout the Octobrists...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.74,0:14:37.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is Hannibal or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.14,0:14:38.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ha... Hanni...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.94,0:14:42.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hungry. I am going to roast Rome.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.15,0:14:46.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know getting old was so scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.28,0:14:53.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Form up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.21,0:15:02.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you guys are actually good soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.67,0:15:04.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Raise up the "Tanegashima" rifle!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.80,0:15:10.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the past week, we've been running\Nmock drills with wooden sticks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.22,0:15:12.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll see how they turn out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.64,0:15:18.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.77,0:15:22.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They look good, but we won't know\Ntill they are actually fired.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.40,0:15:25.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Muskets... Well, we'll see how...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.03,0:15:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe this...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.28,0:15:31.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A matchlock gunner squad has been formed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.26,0:15:36.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, this is a gun... I \Nam scared... sort of...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.95,0:15:39.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We rushed through production\Nto provide 100 muskets.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.71,0:15:42.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As expected, it was impossible\Nfor us to make more.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.92,0:15:45.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the quality should be good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.06,0:15:48.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, we made this toy to see how it works.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.68,0:15:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.18,0:16:01.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're laughing.\NThey're laughing for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.35,0:16:03.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The barbaric tribe in that \Nregion is very scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.11,0:16:09.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobunaga will lead the musketeers.\NHe will set their formations.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.03,0:16:13.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will lead the Dwarves.\NThey will be the foot soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.62,0:16:18.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoichi will lead the Elves.\NThey will be the skirmishers and archers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.20,0:16:22.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will draw the enemy close\Nand annihilate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.87,0:16:25.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We won't let even a single\Nsoldier leave here alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.46,0:16:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-We don't need to completely\Nannihilate them, do we?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.63,0:16:31.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They only came to steal Orte.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.17,0:16:33.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, they'll probably withdraw\Nif they find out that's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.05,0:16:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll slaughter them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.22,0:16:37.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what the soldiers \Nwho run try to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.22,0:16:38.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.14,0:16:43.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You... You don't know much about battle\Ndespite having such broad knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.14,0:16:45.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.40,0:16:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I were them,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.81,0:16:49.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would change my plan the moment I found out
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.08,0:16:50.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it was impossible to conquer the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.28,0:16:54.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The goal would be changed\Nfrom conquest to persecution.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.49,0:16:57.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would kill, kidnap, and rape people...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.99,0:17:00.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would seize and burn \Nany occupied territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.12,0:17:03.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, while returning to the fortress,\NI would assault all the villages on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.37,0:17:04.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be disastrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.46,0:17:06.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they can no longer manipulate the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.95,0:17:08.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,aristocrats, pulling strings \Nto control the empire,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.95,0:17:10.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they will shift to this plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.38,0:17:15.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This so-called Black King's plan is to\Ndestroy the world in the first place, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.38,0:17:18.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he doesn't have any intention to govern it,\Nit will be completely in disarray.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.97,0:17:23.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, the best course of action would\Nbe to allow them to attack Orte for a bit,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.27,0:17:26.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then step in to save the empire, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.85,0:17:29.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll behead them all! Prepare yourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.94,0:17:31.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is what war is all about!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.82,0:17:34.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready! Take positions!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.50,0:17:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.75,0:17:47.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Olminu! Can you hear me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.42,0:17:50.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Relay all communications transmitted\Nthrough the crystal spheres!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.88,0:17:52.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will relay conversations.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.63,0:17:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have never done this before, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.63,0:17:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I'll try.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.19,0:18:10.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're coming... Coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.73,0:18:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're coming... right \Nat us... Coming over...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.49,0:18:18.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come. Come. Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.28,0:18:20.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.62,0:18:22.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Musketeers, load your weapons!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.70,0:18:24.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Form a line!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.91,0:18:28.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is this world's first \Never experience with gunfire.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.39,0:18:30.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are the harbingers!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.00,0:18:33.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are leading from the cutting edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.68,0:18:37.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hundreds of millions of guns\Nshall follow after you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.84,0:18:41.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You all are now standing\Non the precipice of history!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.47,0:18:45.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it. Not yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.44,0:18:47.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.02,0:18:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.27,0:18:53.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it. Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.57,0:18:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A bit closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.03,0:18:57.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.99,0:19:00.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.67,0:19:16.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The forceful power of the gun...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.63,0:19:19.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...plus gunsmoke and gunfire\Nwitnessed for the first time...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.59,0:19:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...minus their inexperience...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.26,0:19:23.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sum of these effects...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.64,0:19:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is powerful...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.68,0:19:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really, a powerful thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.14,0:19:32.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Olminu! Signal Yoichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.65,0:19:35.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yoichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.11,0:19:39.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's really incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.15,0:19:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is... that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.91,0:19:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't just keep hanging back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.54,0:19:47.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aim for center mass. Rain \Narrows down on them!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.42,0:19:55.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect timing!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.39,0:19:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These spheres are really incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.71,0:20:00.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is great.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.17,0:20:03.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could take this back in time\Nand use it in the Battle of Okehazama.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.02,0:20:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Slow... Really slow, as expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.60,0:20:16.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One more volley... Just one\Nmore volley will decide it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.52,0:20:18.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I shouldn't pressure them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.90,0:20:21.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't rush! Ensure the quantity is right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.24,0:20:23.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No need to get in a rush!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.41,0:20:25.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Second volley...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.45,0:20:29.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.09,0:20:40.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The core value of "Tanegashima" lies\Nnot in stopping power or range...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.63,0:20:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Tanegashima" rules with fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.68,0:20:46.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the sound and smoke rise,\Nsomeone is going to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.68,0:20:48.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The moment the second volley hits,\Nthey realize that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.43,0:20:51.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The moment that is understood...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.85,0:20:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...they can no longer charge forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.77,0:20:59.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that moment, if they stop\Nmoving their faltering feet...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.15,0:21:02.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Charge forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.74,0:21:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The warriors plunge into the enemy,\Ncarving through both mind and body.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.03,0:21:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The human musketeers led by Nobunaga,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.21,0:21:16.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Elven archers led by Yoichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.40,0:21:22.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.63,0:21:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the Dwarven shock troopers\Nled by Devil Shimazu...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.10,0:21:30.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would be the optimum solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.15,0:21:46.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shimazu...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.53,0:21:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shimazu!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.53,0:21:51.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shimazu!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.24,0:21:54.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.25,0:21:56.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.88,0:23:26.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Way of the Warrior"
